  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Exodus 24:4",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 24:4",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And Moses wrote the words of the Lord ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That there might be no mistake; as God dictated them on the mount, where, it has been thought by many, God taught him the use of letters; these Moses taught the Israelites, from whom they afterward travelled to Greece and other nations. As soon as God had separated to himself a peculiar people, he governed them by a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "written word, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as he has done ever since, and will do while the world stands. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Pillars according to the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "number of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "tribes — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "These were to represent the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "people, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the other party to the covenant; and we may suppose they were set up ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "over against ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the altar, and that Moses, as mediator, passed to and fro between them. Probably each tribe ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "set up ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "knew ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "its own pillar, and their elders stood by it. He then appointed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sacrifices ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to be offered upon the altar.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
